  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.10.14`\r\nOS & Version: Windows\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nWhen using eth_signTransacion or eth_sendTransaction declaring `\"type\": \"0x2\"` **should** use a type 2 transaction.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nThe transaction type is determined by the pricing method. So when `gasPrice` is used the transaction will be a Legacy tx, and when `maxFeePerGas` and `maxPriorityFeePerGas` are used the transaction will be a type 2 tx.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behavior\r\nSign or send a type 2 transaction with `gasPrice` instead of `MFPG` and `MPFPG` and it will actually be a Legacy tx.",
